INPUT_Element_1_AboutSectionType4_text3d:
Given the magnitude of the crisis, there are some who think that the only way to respond is to fundamentally change who we are. To do and be less.

We, at Prometheus, think this would be a terrible mistake. We believe we can meet this epic challenge not in spite of, but because of who we are.

The urge to discover what lies beyond that far horizon, or that ocean, or this planet, is part of what makes us human. We are explorers and adventurers. We search for inspiration, for whats new and whats next. And we yearn to live better, larger lives. Throughout human existence, this restless impulse has led our species to overcome near unfathomable hardships. And its exactly this ability that we need now.

We shouldnt shrink the scope of human experience. Instead, our goal should be to break the historical link between energy and the dirty fossil fuels that are destroying our world. Instead, we should make energy and the things we do with it in a brand new way.

This is our mission at Prometheus. We are propelled by the future we imagineone in which everyone who wants to can experience the joy of a road trip, the thrill of flight, and, one day soon, the humbling awe of viewing the Earth from orbit.

INPUT_Element_2_AboutSectionType2_text3d:
The pivotal moment that created Prometheus came in October of 2018 after two landmark events. The first was when the United Nations scientific panel on climate change released a dire report. In a list of scenes, it laid out, in graphic detail, the staggering destruction the world was all but certain to suffer in just a few short years. There was still time, the report said, to stop climate change and avoid the worst impacts. But only if the world took immediate, radical steps, not just to curb new emissions, but to remove CO2 from the air.

Heeding this call, two weeks later, Y Combinator, the acclaimed Silicon Valley accelerator, put out a request: any founder with an idea for how to remove that CO2 from the air should step forward. Its time to take big swings at this, it said.

We knew we had to act. That winter, Prometheus was accepted to Y Combinator and launched on Demo Day the following March. Before a packed auditorium, Prometheus founder and CEO, Rob McGinnis explained how the company could pull CO2 from the air and turn it into jet fuel, diesel, and gasoline that were atomically identical to their fossil counterparts. Not only would Prometheuss fuels be 100% carbon neutral, their production could be scaled in time to save the Earth.

INPUT_Element_2_section4_text3d_text: During this step, oxygen is released, making our Forge a kind of mechanical forest. How much oxygen? In one year, a single Titan Fuel Forge will emit 2.25 million kilograms of O2 or roughly the same amount of oxygen emitted by 225 acres of forest.

INPUT_Element_2_section5_text3d_text: In Stage Three, the alcohols are harvested using a special type of membrane called the Maxwell Core. Its pores are carbon nanotubes, which allow alcohols through while rejecting water.

INPUT_Element_2_section6_text3d_text: In Stage Four, a final catalyst step combines the alcohols and recovers water. This step can be customized to produce gasoline, diesel, or jet fuel.
